#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:42
msgid "Declaring options"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:44
msgid ""
"We will need some helper functions, which will come from the [Nixpkgs "
"library](https://github.com/NixOS/nixpkgs/tree/master/lib), which is passed "
"by the module system as `lib`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:46
msgid ""
"- { ... }:\n"
"+ { lib, ... }:\n"
"{\n"
"\n"
"}"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:55
msgid ""
"Using [`lib.mkOption`](https://nixos.org/manual/nixpkgs/stable/#function-"
"library-lib.options.mkOption), declare the `scripts.output` option to have "
"the type `lines`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:57
msgid ""
" { lib, ... }: {\n"
"\n"
"+ options = {\n"
"+   scripts.output = lib.mkOption {\n"
"+     type = lib.types.lines;\n"
"+   };\n"
"+ };\n"
"\n"
" }"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:70
msgid ""
"The `lines` type means that the only valid values are strings, and that "
"multiple definitions should be joined with newlines."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:73
msgid ""
"The name and attribute path of the option is arbitrary. Here we use "
"`scripts`, because we will add another script later, and call this one "
"`output`, because it will output the resulting map."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:77
msgid "Evaluating modules"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:79
msgid ""
"Write a new file `eval.nix` to call [`lib.evalModules`](https://nixos.org/"
"manual/nixpkgs/unstable/#module-system-lib-evalModules) and evaluate the "
"module in `default.nix`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:81
#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:178
msgid "eval.nix"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:81
msgid ""
"let\n"
"  nixpkgs = fetchTarball \"https://github.com/NixOS/nixpkgs/tarball/"
"nixos-23.11\";\n"
"  pkgs = import nixpkgs { config = {}; overlays = []; };\n"
"in\n"
"pkgs.lib.evalModules {\n"
"  modules = [\n"
"    ./default.nix\n"
"  ];\n"
"}"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:94
msgid "Run the following command:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:97
msgid "This will result in an error."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:100
msgid "nix-instantiate --eval eval.nix -A config.scripts.output\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:0
msgid "Detailed explanation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:105
msgid ""
"[`nix-instantiate --eval`](https://nix.dev/manual/nix/stable/command-ref/nix-"
"instantiate) parses and evaluates the Nix file at the specified path, and "
"prints the result. `evalModules` produces an attribute set where the final "
"configuration values appear in the `config` attribute. Therefore we evaluate "
"the Nix expression in `eval.nix` at the [attribute path](https://nix.dev/"
"manual/nix/stable/language/operators#attribute-selection) `config.scripts."
"output`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:110
msgid ""
"The error message indicates that the `scripts.output` option is used but not "
"defined: a value must be set for the option before accessing it. You will do "
"this in the next steps."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:113
msgid "Type checking"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:115
msgid "As previously mentioned, the `lines` type only permits string values."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:118
msgid ""
"In this section, you will set an invalid value and encounter a type error."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:121
msgid "What happens if you instead try to assign an integer to the option?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:123
msgid "Add the following lines to `default.nix`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:125
msgid ""
" { lib, ... }: {\n"
"\n"
"  options = {\n"
"    scripts.output = lib.mkOption {\n"
"      type = lib.types.lines;\n"
"    };\n"
"  };\n"
"\n"
"+ config = {\n"
"+   scripts.output = 42;\n"
"+ };\n"
" }"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:141
msgid ""
"Now try to execute the previous command, and witness your first module error:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:143
msgid ""
"$ nix-instantiate --eval eval.nix -A config.scripts.output\n"
"error:\n"
"...\n"
"       error: A definition for option `scripts.output' is not of type "
"`strings concatenated with \"\\n\"'. Definition values:\n"
"       - In `/home/nix-user/default.nix': 42\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:151
msgid ""
"The definition `scripts.output = 42;` caused a type error: integers are not "
"strings concatenated with the newline character."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:153
msgid ""
"To make this module pass the type checks and successfully evaluate the "
"`scripts.output` option, you will now assign a string to `scripts.output`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:155
msgid ""
"In this case, you will assign a shell command that runs the {download}`map "
"<files/map.sh>` script in the current directory. That in turn calls the "
"Google Maps Static API to generate a world map. The output is passed on to "
"display it with [`feh`](https://feh.finalrewind.org/), a minimalistic image "
"viewer."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:159
msgid ""
"Update `default.nix` by changing the value of `scripts.output` to the "
"following string:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:161
msgid ""
"   config = {\n"
"-    scripts.output = 42;\n"
"+    scripts.output = ''\n"
"+      ./map.sh size=640x640 scale=2 | feh -\n"
"+    '';\n"
"   };"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:171
msgid "Interlude: reproducible scripts"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:173
msgid ""
"That simple command will likely not work as intended on your system, as it "
"may lack the required dependencies (curl and feh). We can solve this by "
"packaging the raw {download}`map <files/map.sh>` script with `pkgs."
"writeShellApplication`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:176
msgid ""
"First, make available a `pkgs` argument in your module evaluation by adding "
"a module that sets `config._module.args`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:178
msgid ""
" pkgs.lib.evalModules {\n"
"   modules = [\n"
"+    ({ config, ... }: { config._module.args = { inherit pkgs; }; })\n"
"     ./default.nix\n"
"   ];\n"
" }"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:189
msgid ""
"This mechanism is currently only [documented in the module system code]"
"(https://github.com/NixOS/nixpkgs/blob/master/lib/modules.nix#L140-L182), "
"and that documentation is incomplete and out of date."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:192
msgid "Then change `default.nix` to have the following contents:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:194
msgid ""
"{ pkgs, lib, ... }: {\n"
"\n"
"  options = {\n"
"    scripts.output = lib.mkOption {\n"
"      type = lib.types.package;\n"
"    };\n"
"  };\n"
"\n"
"  config = {\n"
"    scripts.output = pkgs.writeShellApplication {\n"
"      name = \"map\";\n"
"      runtimeInputs = with pkgs; [ curl feh ];\n"
"      text = ''\n"
"        ${./map.sh} size=640x640 scale=2 | feh -\n"
"      '';\n"
"    };\n"
"  };\n"
"}"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:216
msgid ""
"This will access the previously added `pkgs` argument so we can use "
"dependencies, and copy the `map` file in the current directory into the Nix "
"store so it's available to the wrapped script, which will also live in the "
"Nix store."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:218
msgid "Run the script with:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:220
msgid ""
"nix-build eval.nix -A config.scripts.output\n"
"./result/bin/map\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:225
msgid ""
"To iterate more quickly, open a new terminal and set up [`entr`](https://"
"github.com/eradman/entr) to re-run the script whenever any source file in "
"the current directory changes:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:227
msgid ""
"nix-shell -p entr findutils bash --run \\\n"
"  \"ls *.nix | \\\n"
"   entr -rs ' \\\n"
"     nix-build eval.nix -A config.scripts.output --no-out-link \\\n"
"     | xargs printf -- \\\"%s/bin/map\\\" \\\n"
"     | xargs bash \\\n"
"   ' \\\n"
"  \"\n"
msgstr ""

