#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:246
msgid "Declaring more options"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:248
msgid ""
"Rather than setting all script parameters directly, we will do that through "
"the module system. This will not just add some safety through type checking, "
"but also allow building abstractions to manage growing complexity and "
"changing requirements."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:251
msgid ""
"Let's begin by introducing another option, `requestParams`, which will "
"represent the parameters of the request made to the Google Maps API."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:253
msgid ""
"Its type will be `listOf <elementType>`, which is a list of elements of one "
"type."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:255
msgid ""
"Instead of `lines`, in this case you will want the type of the list elements "
"to be `str`, a generic string type."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:257
msgid ""
"The difference between `str` and `lines` is in their merging behavior: "
"Module option types not only check for valid values, but also specify how "
"multiple definitions of an option are to be combined into one."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:259
msgid ""
"For `lines`, multiple definitions get merged by concatenation with newlines."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:260
msgid ""
"For `str`, multiple definitions are not allowed. This is not a problem here, "
"since one can't define a list element multiple times."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:262
msgid "Make the following additions to your `default.nix` file:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:264
msgid ""
"     scripts.output = lib.mkOption {\n"
"       type = lib.types.package;\n"
"     };\n"
"+\n"
"+    requestParams = lib.mkOption {\n"
"+      type = lib.types.listOf lib.types.str;\n"
"+    };\n"
"   };\n"
"\n"
"  config = {\n"
"    scripts.output = pkgs.writeShellApplication {\n"
"      name = \"map\";\n"
"      runtimeInputs = with pkgs; [ curl feh ];\n"
"      text = ''\n"
"        ${./map.sh} size=640x640 scale=2 | feh -\n"
"      '';\n"
"    };\n"
"+\n"
"+    requestParams = [\n"
"+      \"size=640x640\"\n"
"+      \"scale=2\"\n"
"+    ];\n"
"   };\n"
" }"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:292
msgid "Dependencies between options"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:294
msgid ""
"A given module generally declares one option that produces a result to be "
"used elsewhere, in this case `scripts.output`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:296
msgid ""
"Options can depend on other options, making it possible to build more useful "
"abstractions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:298
msgid ""
"Here, we want the `scripts.output` option to use the values of "
"`requestParams` as arguments to the `./map` script."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:300
msgid "Accessing option values"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:302
msgid ""
"To make option values available to a module, the arguments of the function "
"declaring the module must include the `config` attribute."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:304
msgid "Update `default.nix` to add the `config` attribute:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:306
msgid ""
"-{ pkgs, lib, ... }: {\n"
"+{ pkgs, lib, config, ... }: {"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:312
msgid ""
"When a module that sets options is evaluated, the resulting values can be "
"accessed by their corresponding attribute names under `config`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:315
msgid "Option values can't be accessed directly from the same module."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:317
msgid ""
"The module system evaluates all modules it receives, and any of them can "
"define a particular option's value. What happens when an option is set by "
"multiple modules is determined by that option's type."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:322
msgid ""
"The `config` *argument* is **not** the same as the `config` *attribute*:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:323
msgid ""
"The `config` *argument* holds the result of the module system's lazy "
"evaluation, which takes into account all modules passed to `evalModules` and "
"their `imports`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:324
msgid ""
"The `config` *attribute* of a module exposes that particular module's option "
"values to the module system for evaluation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:327
msgid "Now make the following changes to `default.nix`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:329
msgid ""
"   config = {\n"
"     scripts.output = pkgs.writeShellApplication {\n"
"       name = \"map\";\n"
"       runtimeInputs = with pkgs; [ curl feh ];\n"
"       text = ''\n"
"-        ${./map.sh} size=640x640 scale=2 | feh -\n"
"+        ${./map.sh} ${lib.concatStringsSep \" \"\n"
"+          config.requestParams} | feh -\n"
"       '';"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:342
msgid ""
"Here, the value of the `config.requestParams` attribute is populated by the "
"module system based on the definitions in the same file."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:345
msgid ""
"Lazy evaluation in the Nix language allows the module system to make a value "
"available in the `config` argument passed to the module which defines that "
"value."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:348
msgid ""
"`lib.concatStringsSep \" \"` is then used to join each list element from the "
"value of `config.requestParams` into a single string, with the list elements "
"of `requestParams` separated by a space character."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:350
msgid ""
"The result of this represents the list of command line arguments to pass to "
"the `./map` script."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:352
msgid "Conditional definitions"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:353
msgid ""
"Sometimes, you will want option values to be optional. This can be useful "
"when defining a value for an option is not required, as in the following "
"case."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:355
msgid ""
"You will define a new option, `map.zoom`, to control the zoom level of the "
"map. The Google Maps API will infer a zoom level if no corresponding "
"argument is passed, a situation you can represent with the `nullOr <type>`, "
"which represents values of type `<type>` or `null`. This _does not_ "
"automatically mean that when the option isn't defined, the value of such an "
"option is `null` -- we still need to define a default value."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:357
msgid ""
"Add the `map` attribute set with the `zoom` option into the top-level "
"`options` declaration, like so:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:359
msgid ""
"     requestParams = lib.mkOption {\n"
"       type = lib.types.listOf lib.types.str;\n"
"     };\n"
"+\n"
"+    map = {\n"
"+      zoom = lib.mkOption {\n"
"+        type = lib.types.nullOr lib.types.int;\n"
"+        default = null;\n"
"+      };\n"
"+    };\n"
"   };"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:374
msgid ""
"To make use of this, use the `mkIf <condition> <definition>` function, which "
"only adds the definition if the condition evaluates to `true`. Make the "
"following additions to the `requestParams` list in the `config` block:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:377
msgid ""
"     requestParams = [\n"
"       \"size=640x640\"\n"
"       \"scale=2\"\n"
"+      (lib.mkIf (config.map.zoom != null)\n"
"+        \"zoom=${toString config.map.zoom}\")\n"
"     ];\n"
"   };"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:388
msgid ""
"This will only add a `zoom` parameter to the script invocation if the value "
"of `config.map.zoom` is not `null`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:390
msgid "Default values"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:392
msgid ""
"Let's say that in our application we want to have a different default "
"behavior that sets the zoom level to `10`, such that automatic zooming has "
"to be enabled explicitly."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:394
msgid ""
"This can be done with the `default` argument to [`mkOption`](https://github."
"com/NixOS/nixpkgs/blob/master/lib/options.nix). Its value will be used if "
"the value of the option declaring it is not specified otherwise."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:397
msgid "Modify the corresponding line:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:399
msgid ""
"     map = {\n"
"       zoom = lib.mkOption {\n"
"         type = lib.types.nullOr lib.types.int;\n"
"-        default = null;\n"
"+        default = 10;\n"
"       };\n"
"     };\n"
"   };"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:411
msgid "Wrapping shell commands"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:413
msgid ""
"You have now declared options controlling the map dimensions and zoom level, "
"but have not provided a way to specify where the map should be centered."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:415
msgid ""
"Add the `center` option now, possibly with your own location as default "
"value:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:417
msgid ""
"         type = lib.types.nullOr lib.types.int;\n"
"         default = 10;\n"
"       };\n"
"+\n"
"+      center = lib.mkOption {\n"
"+        type = lib.types.nullOr lib.types.str;\n"
"+        default = \"switzerland\";\n"
"+      };\n"
"     };\n"
"   };"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:431
msgid ""
"To implement this behavior, you will use the {download}`geocode <files/"
"geocode.sh>` utility, which turns location names into coordinates. There are "
"multiple ways of making a new package accessible, but as an exercise, you "
"will add it as an option in the module system."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:434
msgid "First, add a new option to accommodate the package:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:437
msgid ""
"   options = {\n"
"     scripts.output = lib.mkOption {\n"
"       type = lib.types.package;\n"
"     };\n"
"+\n"
"+    scripts.geocode = lib.mkOption {\n"
"+      type = lib.types.package;\n"
"+    };"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:449
msgid ""
"Then define the value for that option where you make the raw script "
"reproducible by wrapping a call to it in `writeShellApplication`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:451
msgid ""
"   config = {\n"
"+    scripts.geocode = pkgs.writeShellApplication {\n"
"+      name = \"geocode\";\n"
"+      runtimeInputs = with pkgs; [ curl jq ];\n"
"+      text = ''exec ${./geocode.sh} \"$@\"'';\n"
"+    };\n"
"+\n"
"     scripts.output = pkgs.writeShellApplication {\n"
"       name = \"map\";\n"
"       runtimeInputs = with pkgs; [ curl feh ];"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:465
msgid ""
"Add another `mkIf` call to the list of `requestParams` now where you access "
"the wrapped package through `config.scripts.geocode`, and run the executable "
"`/bin/geocode` inside:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:467
msgid ""
"       \"scale=2\"\n"
"       (lib.mkIf (config.map.zoom != null)\n"
"         \"zoom=${toString config.map.zoom}\")\n"
"+      (lib.mkIf (config.map.center != null)\n"
"+        \"center=\\\"$(${config.scripts.geocode}/bin/geocode ${\n"
"+          lib.escapeShellArg config.map.center\n"
"+        })\\\"\")\n"
"     ];\n"
"   };"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:480
msgid ""
"This time, you've used `escapeShellArg` to pass the `config.map.center` "
"value as a command-line argument to `geocode`, string interpolating the "
"result back into the `requestParams` string which sets the `center` value."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:482
msgid ""
"Wrapping shell command execution in Nix modules is a helpful technique for "
"controlling system changes, as it uses the more ergonomic attributes and "
"values interface rather than dealing with the peculiarities of escaping "
"manually."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:484
msgid "Splitting modules"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:486
msgid ""
"The [module schema](https://nixos.org/manual/nixos/stable/#sec-writing-"
"modules) includes the `imports` attribute, which allows incorporating "
"further modules, for example to split a large configuration into multiple "
"files."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:488
msgid ""
"In particular, this allows you to separate option declarations from where "
"they are used in your configuration."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:490
msgid ""
"Create a new module, `marker.nix`, where you can declare options for "
"defining location pins and other markers on the map:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:492
#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:525
#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:555
#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:584
#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:615
#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:633
#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:644
#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:683
#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:702
#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:734
#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:753
#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:770
#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:802
#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:824
#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:840
#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:855
#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:872
#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:888
#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:954
#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:969
#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:984
#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:997
msgid "marker.nix"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:492
msgid ""
"{ lib, config, ... }: {\n"
"\n"
"}"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:499
msgid "Reference this new file in `default.nix` using the `imports` attribute:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:501
msgid ""
" { pkgs, lib, config, ... }: {\n"
"\n"
"+  imports = [\n"
"+    ./marker.nix\n"
"+  ];\n"
"+"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:511
msgid "The `submodule` type"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:513
msgid ""
"We want to set multiple markers on the map. A marker is a complex type with "
"multiple fields."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:516
msgid ""
"This is where one of the most useful types included in the module system's "
"type system comes into play: `submodule`. This type allows you to define "
"nested modules with their own options."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:519
msgid ""
"Here, you will define a new `map.markers` option whose type is a list of "
"submodules, each with a nested `location` type, allowing you to define a "
"list of markers on the map."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:521
msgid ""
"Each assignment of markers will be type-checked during evaluation of the top-"
"level `config`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:523
msgid "Make the following changes to `marker.nix`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:525
msgid ""
"-{ lib, config, ... }: {\n"
"+{ lib, config, ... }:\n"
"+let\n"
"+  markerType = lib.types.submodule {\n"
"+    options = {\n"
"+      location = lib.mkOption {\n"
"+        type = lib.types.nullOr lib.types.str;\n"
"+        default = null;\n"
"+      };\n"
"+    };\n"
"+  };\n"
"+in {\n"
"+\n"
"+  options = {\n"
"+    map.markers = lib.mkOption {\n"
"+      type = lib.types.listOf markerType;\n"
"+    };\n"
"+  };"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:547
msgid "Defining options in other modules"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:549
msgid ""
"Because of the way the module system composes option definitions, you can "
"freely assign values to options defined in other modules."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:551
msgid ""
"In this case, you will use the `map.markers` option to produce and add new "
"elements to the `requestParams` list, making your declared markers appear on "
"the returned map – but from the module declared in `marker.nix`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:553
msgid ""
"To implement this behavior, add the following `config` block to `marker.nix`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:555
msgid ""
"+  config = {\n"
"+\n"
"+    map.markers = [\n"
"+      { location = \"new york\"; }\n"
"+    ];\n"
"+\n"
"+    requestParams = let\n"
"+      paramForMarker =\n"
"+        builtins.map (marker: \"$(${config.scripts.geocode}/bin/geocode ${\n"
"+          lib.escapeShellArg marker.location})\") config.map.markers;\n"
"+    in [ \"markers=\\\"${lib.concatStringsSep \"|\" paramForMarker}\\"
"\"\" ];\n"
"+  };"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:572
msgid ""
"To avoid confusion with the `map` option setting and the final `config.map` "
"configuration value, here we use the `map` function explicitly as `builtins."
"map`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:576
msgid ""
"Here, you again used `escapeShellArg` and string interpolation to generate a "
"Nix string, this time producing a pipe-separated list of geocoded location "
"attributes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:578
msgid ""
"The `requestParams` value was also set to the resulting list of strings, "
"which gets appended to the `requestParams` list defined in `default.nix`, "
"thanks to the default merging behavior of the `list` type."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:580
msgid ""
"When defining multiple markers, determining an appropriate center or zoom "
"level for the map may be challenging; it's easier to let the API do this for "
"you."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:582
msgid ""
"To achieve this, make the following additions to `marker.nix`, above the "
"`requestParams` declaration:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:584
msgid ""
"+    map.center = lib.mkIf\n"
"+      (lib.length config.map.markers >= 1)\n"
"+      null;\n"
"+\n"
"+    map.zoom = lib.mkIf\n"
"+      (lib.length config.map.markers >= 2)\n"
"+      null;\n"
"+\n"
"     requestParams = let\n"
"       paramForMarker = marker:\n"
"         let"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:599
msgid ""
"In this case, the default behavior of the Google Maps API when not passed a "
"center or zoom level is to pick the geometric center of all the given "
"markers, and to set a zoom level appropriate for viewing all markers at once."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:601
msgid "Nested submodules"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:603
msgid ""
"Next, we want to allow multiple named users to define a list of markers each."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:605
msgid ""
"For that you'll add a `users` option with type `lib.types.attrsOf "
"<subtype>`, which will allow you to define `users` as an attribute set, "
"whose values have type `<subtype>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:607
msgid ""
"Here, that subtype will be another submodule which allows declaring a "
"departure marker, suitable for querying the API for the recommended route "
"for a trip."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:609
msgid ""
"This will again make use of the `markerType` submodule, giving a nested "
"structure of submodules."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:611
msgid ""
"To propagate marker definitions from `users` to the `map.markers` option, "
"make the following changes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:613
#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:681
msgid "In the `let` block:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:615
msgid ""
"+  userType = lib.types.submodule {\n"
"+    options = {\n"
"+      departure = lib.mkOption {\n"
"+        type = markerType;\n"
"+        default = {};\n"
"+      };\n"
"+    };\n"
"+  };\n"
"+\n"
" in {"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:629
msgid ""
"This defines a submodule type for a user, with a `departure` option of type "
"`markerType`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:631
msgid "In the `options` block, above `map.markers`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:633
msgid ""
"+    users = lib.mkOption {\n"
"+      type = lib.types.attrsOf userType;\n"
"+    };"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:640
msgid ""
"That allows adding a `users` attribute set to `config` in any submodule that "
"imports `marker.nix`, where each attribute will be of type `userType` as "
"declared in the previous step."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:642
msgid "In the `config` block, above `map.center`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:644
msgid ""
"   config = {\n"
"\n"
"-    map.markers = [\n"
"-      { location = \"new york\"; }\n"
"-    ];\n"
"+    map.markers = lib.filter\n"
"+      (marker: marker.location != null)\n"
"+      (lib.concatMap (user: [\n"
"+        user.departure\n"
"+      ]) (lib.attrValues config.users));\n"
"\n"
"     map.center = lib.mkIf\n"
"       (lib.length config.map.markers >= 1)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:661
msgid ""
"This takes all the `departure` markers from all users in the `config` "
"argument, and adds them to `map.markers` if their `location` attribute is "
"not `null`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:663
msgid ""
"The `config.users` attribute set is passed to `attrValues`, which returns a "
"list of values of each of the attributes in the set (here, the set of "
"`config.users` you've defined), sorted alphabetically (which is how "
"attribute names are stored in the Nix language)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:665
msgid ""
"Back in `default.nix`, the resulting `map.markers` option value is still "
"accessed by `requestParams`, which in turn is used to generate arguments to "
"the script that ultimately calls the Google Maps API."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:667
msgid ""
"Defining the options in this way allows you to set multiple `users.<name>."
"departure.location` values and generate a map with the appropriate zoom and "
"center, with pins corresponding to the set of `departure.location` values "
"for *all* `users`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:669
msgid ""
"In the 2021 Summer of Nix, this formed the basis of an interactive multi-"
"person map demo."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:671
msgid "The `strMatching` type"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:673
msgid ""
"Now that the map can be rendered with multiple markers, it's time to add "
"some style customizations."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:675
msgid ""
"To tell the markers apart, add another option to the `markerType` submodule, "
"to allow labeling each marker pin."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:677
msgid ""
"The API documentation states that [these labels must be either an uppercase "
"letter or a number](https://developers.google.com/maps/documentation/maps-"
"static/start#MarkerStyles)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:679
msgid ""
"You can implement this with the `strMatching \"<regex>\"` type, where "
"`<regex>` is a regular expression that will accept any matching values, in "
"this case an uppercase letter or number."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:683
msgid ""
"         type = lib.types.nullOr lib.types.str;\n"
"         default = null;\n"
"       };\n"
"+\n"
"+      style.label = lib.mkOption {\n"
"+        type = lib.types.nullOr\n"
"+          (lib.types.strMatching \"[A-Z0-9]\");\n"
"+        default = null;\n"
"+      };\n"
"     };\n"
"   };"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:698
msgid ""
"Again, `types.nullOr` allows for `null` values, and the default has been set "
"to `null`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:700
msgid "In the `paramForMarker` function:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:702
msgid ""
"     requestParams = let\n"
"-      paramForMarker =\n"
"-        builtins.map (marker: \"$(${config.scripts.geocode}/bin/geocode ${\n"
"-         lib.escapeShellArg marker.location})\") config.map.markers;\n"
"-    in [ \"markers=\\\"${lib.concatStringsSep \"|\" paramForMarker}\\"
"\"\" ];\n"
"+      paramForMarker = marker:\n"
"+        let\n"
"+          attributes =\n"
"+            lib.optional (marker.style.label != null)\n"
"+            \"label:${marker.style.label}\"\n"
"+            ++ [\n"
"+              \"$(${config.scripts.geocode}/bin/geocode ${\n"
"+                lib.escapeShellArg marker.location\n"
"+              })\"\n"
"+            ];\n"
"+        in \"markers=\\\"${lib.concatStringsSep \"|\" attributes}\\\"\";\n"
"+      in\n"
"+        builtins.map paramForMarker config.map.markers;"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:724
msgid ""
"Note how we now create a unique `marker` for each user by concatenating the "
"`label` and `location` attributes together, and assigning them to the "
"`requestParams`. The label for each `marker` is only propagated to the CLI "
"parameters if `marker.style.label` is set."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:727
msgid "Functions as submodule arguments"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:729
msgid ""
"Right now, if a label is not explicitly set, none will show up. But since "
"every `users` attribute has a name, we could use that as an automatic value "
"instead."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:732
msgid ""
"This `firstUpperAlnum` function allows you to retrieve the first character "
"of the username, with the correct type for passing to `departure.style."
"label`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:734
msgid ""
"{ lib, config, ... }:\n"
" let\n"
"+  # Returns the uppercased first letter\n"
"+  # or number of a string\n"
"+  firstUpperAlnum = str:\n"
"+    lib.mapNullable lib.head\n"
"+    (builtins.match \"[^A-Z0-9]*([A-Z0-9]).*\"\n"
"+    (lib.toUpper str));\n"
"\n"
"   markerType = lib.types.submodule {\n"
"     options = {"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:749
msgid ""
"By transforming the argument to `lib.types.submodule` into a function, you "
"can access arguments within it."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:751
msgid ""
"One special argument automatically available to submodules is `name`, which "
"when used in `attrsOf`, gives you the name of the attribute the submodule is "
"defined under:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:753
msgid ""
"-  userType = lib.types.submodule {\n"
"+  userType = lib.types.submodule ({ name, ... }: {\n"
"     options = {\n"
"       departure = lib.mkOption {\n"
"         type = markerType;\n"
"         default = {};\n"
"       };\n"
"     };\n"
"-  };"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:766
msgid ""
"In this case, you don't easily have access to the name from the marker "
"submodules `label` option, where you otherwise could set a `default` value."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:768
msgid ""
"Instead you can use the `config` section of the `user` submodule to set a "
"default, like so:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:770
msgid ""
"+\n"
"+    config = {\n"
"+      departure.style.label = lib.mkDefault\n"
"+        (firstUpperAlnum name);\n"
"+    };\n"
"+  });\n"
"\n"
" in {"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:784
msgid ""
"Module options have a *priority*, represented as an integer, which "
"determines the precedence for setting the option to a particular value. When "
"merging values, the priority with lowest numeric value wins."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:787
msgid ""
"The `lib.mkDefault` modifier sets the priority of its argument value to "
"1000, the lowest precedence."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:789
msgid "This ensures that other values set for the same option will prevail."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:792
msgid "The `either` and `enum` types"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:794
msgid ""
"For better visual contrast, it would be helpful to have a way to change the "
"*color* of a marker."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:796
msgid "Here you will use two new type-functions for this:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:797
msgid ""
"`either <this> <that>`, which takes two types as arguments, and allows "
"either of them"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:798
msgid ""
"`enum [ <allowed values> ]`, which takes a list of allowed values, and "
"allows any of them"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:800
msgid ""
"In the `let` block, add the following `colorType` option, which can hold "
"strings containing either some given color names or an RGB value, add the "
"new compound type:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:802
msgid ""
"     ...\n"
"     (builtins.match \"[^A-Z0-9]*([A-Z0-9]).*\"\n"
"     (lib.toUpper str));\n"
"\n"
"+  # Either a color name or `0xRRGGBB`\n"
"+  colorType = lib.types.either\n"
"+    (lib.types.strMatching \"0x[0-9A-F]{6}\")\n"
"+    (lib.types.enum [\n"
"+      \"black\" \"brown\" \"green\" \"purple\" \"yellow\"\n"
"+      \"blue\" \"gray\" \"orange\" \"red\" \"white\" ]);\n"
"+\n"
"   markerType = lib.types.submodule {\n"
"     options = {\n"
"       location = lib.mkOption {"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:820
msgid ""
"This allows either strings that match a 24-bit hexadecimal number or are "
"equal to one of the specified color names."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:822
msgid ""
"At the bottom of the `let` block, add the `style.color` option and specify a "
"default value:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:824
msgid ""
"           (lib.types.strMatching \"[A-Z0-9]\");\n"
"         default = null;\n"
"       };\n"
"+\n"
"+      style.color = lib.mkOption {\n"
"+        type = colorType;\n"
"+        default = \"red\";\n"
"+      };\n"
"     };\n"
"   };"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:838
msgid ""
"Now add an entry to the `paramForMarker` list which makes use of the new "
"option:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:840
msgid ""
"               (marker.style.label != null)\n"
"               \"label:${marker.style.label}\"\n"
"             ++ [\n"
"+              \"color:${marker.style.color}\"\n"
"               \"$(${config.scripts.geocode}/bin/geocode ${\n"
"                 lib.escapeShellArg marker.location\n"
"               })\""
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:851
msgid ""
"In case you set many different markers, it would be helpful to have the "
"ability to change their size individually."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:853
msgid ""
"Add a new `style.size` option to `marker.nix`, allowing you to choose from "
"the set of pre-defined sizes:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:855
msgid ""
"         type = colorType;\n"
"         default = \"red\";\n"
"       };\n"
"+\n"
"+      style.size = lib.mkOption {\n"
"+        type = lib.types.enum\n"
"+          [ \"tiny\" \"small\" \"medium\" \"large\" ];\n"
"+        default = \"medium\";\n"
"+      };\n"
"     };\n"
"   };"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:870
msgid ""
"Now add a mapping for the size parameter in `paramForMarker`, which selects "
"an appropriate string to pass to the API:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:872
msgid ""
"     requestParams = let\n"
"       paramForMarker = marker:\n"
"         let\n"
"+          size = {\n"
"+            tiny = \"tiny\";\n"
"+            small = \"small\";\n"
"+            medium = \"mid\";\n"
"+            large = null;\n"
"+          }.${marker.style.size};\n"
"+"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:886
msgid ""
"Finally, add another `lib.optional` call to the `attributes` string, making "
"use of the selected size:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:888
msgid ""
"           attributes =\n"
"             lib.optional\n"
"               (marker.style.label != null)\n"
"               \"label:${marker.style.label}\"\n"
"+            ++ lib.optional\n"
"+              (size != null)\n"
"+              \"size:${size}\"\n"
"             ++ [\n"
"               \"color:${marker.style.color}\"\n"
"               \"$(${config.scripts.geocode}/bin/geocode ${"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:902
msgid "The `pathType` submodule"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:904
msgid ""
"So far, you've created an option for declaring a *departure* marker, as well "
"as several options for configuring the marker's visual representation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:906
msgid ""
"Now we want to compute and display a route from the user's location to some "
"destination."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:908
msgid ""
"The new option defined in the next section will allow you to set an "
"*arrival* marker, which together with a departure allows you to draw *paths* "
"on the map using the new module defined below."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:910
msgid "To start, create a new `path.nix` file with the following contents:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:912
#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:1013
#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:1045
#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:1070
#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:1088
#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:1110
#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:1131
#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:1150
#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:1168
#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:1184
#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:1203
#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:1219
msgid "path.nix"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:912
msgid ""
"{ lib, config, ... }:\n"
"let\n"
"  pathType = lib.types.submodule {\n"
"    options = {\n"
"      locations = lib.mkOption {\n"
"        type = lib.types.listOf lib.types.str;\n"
"      };\n"
"    };\n"
"  };\n"
"in\n"
"{\n"
"  options = {\n"
"    map.paths = lib.mkOption {\n"
"      type = lib.types.listOf pathType;\n"
"    };\n"
"  };\n"
"  config = {\n"
"    requestParams =\n"
"      let\n"
"        attrForLocation = loc:\n"
"          \"$(${config.scripts.geocode}/bin/geocode ${lib.escapeShellArg "
"loc})\";\n"
"        paramForPath = path:\n"
"          let\n"
"            attributes =\n"
"              builtins.map attrForLocation path.locations;\n"
"          in\n"
"          ''path=\"${lib.concatStringsSep \"|\" attributes}\"'';\n"
"      in\n"
"      builtins.map paramForPath config.map.paths;\n"
"  };\n"
"}"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:947
msgid ""
"The `path.nix` module declares an option for defining a list of paths on our "
"`map`, where each path is a list of strings for geographic locations."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:950
msgid ""
"In the `config` attribute we augment the API call by setting the "
"`requestParams` option value with the coordinates transformed appropriately, "
"which will be concatenated with request parameters set elsewhere."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:952
msgid "Now import this new `path.nix` module from your `marker.nix` module:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:954
msgid ""
" in {\n"
"\n"
"+  imports = [\n"
"+    ./path.nix\n"
"+  ];\n"
"+\n"
"   options = {\n"
"\n"
"     users = lib.mkOption {"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:967
msgid ""
"Copy the `departure` option declaration to a new `arrival` option in `marker."
"nix`, to complete the initial path implementation:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:969
msgid ""
"         type = markerType;\n"
"         default = {};\n"
"       };\n"
"+\n"
"+      arrival = lib.mkOption {\n"
"+        type = markerType;\n"
"+        default = {};\n"
"+      };\n"
"     };"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:982
msgid ""
"Next, add an `arrival.style.label` attribute to the `config` block, "
"mirroring the `departure.style.label`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:984
msgid ""
"     config = {\n"
"       departure.style.label = lib.mkDefault\n"
"         (firstUpperAlnum name);\n"
"+      arrival.style.label = lib.mkDefault\n"
"+        (firstUpperAlnum name);\n"
"     };\n"
"   });"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:995
msgid ""
"Finally, update the return list in the function passed to `concatMap` in "
"`map.markers` to also include the `arrival` marker for each user:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:997
msgid ""
"     map.markers = lib.filter\n"
"       (marker: marker.location != null)\n"
"       (lib.concatMap (user: [\n"
"-        user.departure\n"
"+        user.departure user.arrival\n"
"       ]) (lib.attrValues config.users));\n"
"\n"
"     map.center = lib.mkIf"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:1009
msgid ""
"Now you have the basis to define paths on the map, connecting pairs of "
"departure and arrival points."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:1011
msgid ""
"In the path module, define a path connecting every user's departure and "
"arrival locations:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:1013
msgid ""
"   config = {\n"
"+\n"
"+    map.paths = builtins.map (user: {\n"
"+      locations = [\n"
"+        user.departure.location\n"
"+        user.arrival.location\n"
"+      ];\n"
"+    }) (lib.filter (user:\n"
"+      user.departure.location != null\n"
"+      && user.arrival.location != null\n"
"+    ) (lib.attrValues config.users));\n"
"+\n"
"     requestParams = let\n"
"       attrForLocation = loc:\n"
"         \"$(geocode ${lib.escapeShellArg loc})\";"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:1032
msgid ""
"The new `map.paths` attribute contains a list of all valid paths defined for "
"all users."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:1034
msgid ""
"A path is valid only if the `departure` and `arrival` attributes are set for "
"that user."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:1036
msgid "The `between` constraint on integer values"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:1038
msgid ""
"Your users have spoken, and they demand the ability to customize the styles "
"of their paths with a `weight` option."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:1040
msgid "As before, you'll now declare a new submodule for the path style."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:1042
msgid ""
"While you could also directly declare the `style.weight` option, in this "
"case you should use the submodule to be able to reuse the path style type "
"later."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:1044
msgid ""
"Add the `pathStyleType` submodule option to the `let` block in `path.nix`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:1045
msgid ""
" { lib, config, ... }:\n"
" let\n"
"+\n"
"+  pathStyleType = lib.types.submodule {\n"
"+    options = {\n"
"+      weight = lib.mkOption {\n"
"+        type = lib.types.ints.between 1 20;\n"
"+        default = 5;\n"
"+      };\n"
"+    };\n"
"+  };\n"
"+\n"
"   pathType = lib.types.submodule {"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:1063
msgid ""
"The `ints.between <lower> <upper>` type allows integers in the given "
"(inclusive) range."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:1066
msgid ""
"The path weight will default to 5, but can be set to any integer value in "
"the 1 to 20 range, with higher weights producing thicker paths on the map."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:1068
msgid "Now add a `style` option to the `options` set further down the file:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:1070
msgid ""
"     options = {\n"
"       locations = lib.mkOption {\n"
"         type = lib.types.listOf lib.types.str;\n"
"       };\n"
"+\n"
"+      style = lib.mkOption {\n"
"+        type = pathStyleType;\n"
"+        default = {};\n"
"+      };\n"
"     };\n"
"\n"
"   };"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:1086
msgid "Finally, update the `attributes` list in `paramForPath`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:1088
msgid ""
"       paramForPath = path:\n"
"         let\n"
"           attributes =\n"
"-            builtins.map attrForLocation path.locations;\n"
"+            [\n"
"+              \"weight:${toString path.style.weight}\"\n"
"+            ]\n"
"+            ++ builtins.map attrForLocation path.locations;\n"
"         in \"path=\\\"${lib.concatStringsSep \"|\" attributes}\\\"\";"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:1101
msgid "The `pathStyle` submodule"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:1103
msgid ""
"Users still cannot actually customize the path style yet. Introduce a new "
"`pathStyle` option for each user."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:1106
msgid ""
"The module system allows you to declare values for an option multiple times, "
"and if the types permit doing so, takes care of merging each declaration's "
"values together."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:1108
msgid ""
"This makes it possible to have a definition for the `users` option in the "
"`marker.nix` module, as well as a `users` definition in `path.nix`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:1110
msgid ""
" in {\n"
"   options = {\n"
"+\n"
"+    users = lib.mkOption {\n"
"+      type = lib.types.attrsOf (lib.types.submodule {\n"
"+        options.pathStyle = lib.mkOption {\n"
"+          type = pathStyleType;\n"
"+          default = {};\n"
"+        };\n"
"+      });\n"
"+    };\n"
"+\n"
"     map.paths = lib.mkOption {\n"
"       type = lib.types.listOf pathType;\n"
"     };"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:1129
msgid ""
"Then add a line using the `user.pathStyle` option in `map.paths` where each "
"user's paths are processed:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:1131
msgid ""
"         user.departure.location\n"
"         user.arrival.location\n"
"       ];\n"
"+      style = user.pathStyle;\n"
"     }) (lib.filter (user:\n"
"       user.departure.location != null\n"
"       && user.arrival.location != null"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:1142
msgid "Path styling: color"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:1144
msgid "As with markers, paths should have customizable colors."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:1146
msgid "You can accomplish this using types you've already encountered by now."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:1148
msgid ""
"Add a new `colorType` block to `path.nix`, specifying the allowed color "
"names and RGB/RGBA hexadecimal values:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:1150
msgid ""
" { lib, config, ... }:\n"
" let\n"
"\n"
"+  # Either a color name, `0xRRGGBB` or `0xRRGGBBAA`\n"
"+  colorType = lib.types.either\n"
"+    (lib.types.strMatching \"0x[0-9A-F]{6}([0-9A-F]{2})?\")\n"
"+    (lib.types.enum [\n"
"+      \"black\" \"brown\" \"green\" \"purple\" \"yellow\"\n"
"+      \"blue\" \"gray\" \"orange\" \"red\" \"white\"\n"
"+    ]);\n"
"+\n"
"   pathStyleType = lib.types.submodule {"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:1166
msgid ""
"Under the `weight` option, add a new `color` option to use the new "
"`colorType` value:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:1168
msgid ""
"         type = lib.types.ints.between 1 20;\n"
"         default = 5;\n"
"       };\n"
"+\n"
"+      color = lib.mkOption {\n"
"+        type = colorType;\n"
"+        default = \"blue\";\n"
"+      };\n"
"     };\n"
"   };"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:1182
msgid "Finally, add a line using the `color` option to the `attributes` list:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:1184
msgid ""
"           attributes =\n"
"             [\n"
"               \"weight:${toString path.style.weight}\"\n"
"+              \"color:${path.style.color}\"\n"
"             ]\n"
"             ++ map attrForLocation path.locations;\n"
"         in \"path=${"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:1195
msgid "Further styling"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:1197
msgid ""
"Now that you've got this far, to further improve the aesthetics of the "
"rendered map, add another style option allowing paths to be drawn as "
"*geodesics*, the shortest \"as the crow flies\" distance between two points "
"on Earth."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:1199
msgid ""
"Since this feature can be turned on or off, you can do this using the `bool` "
"type, which can be `true` or `false`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:1201
msgid "Make the following changes to `path.nix` now:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:1203
msgid ""
"         type = colorType;\n"
"         default = \"blue\";\n"
"       };\n"
"+\n"
"+      geodesic = lib.mkOption {\n"
"+        type = lib.types.bool;\n"
"+        default = false;\n"
"+      };\n"
"     };\n"
"   };"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:1217
msgid ""
"Make sure to also add a line to use that value in `attributes` list, so the "
"option value is included in the API call:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:1219
msgid ""
"             [\n"
"               \"weight:${toString path.style.weight}\"\n"
"               \"color:${path.style.color}\"\n"
"+              \"geodesic:${lib.boolToString path.style.geodesic}\"\n"
"             ]\n"
"             ++ map attrForLocation path.locations;\n"
"         in \"path=${"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:1230
msgid "Wrapping up"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:1232
msgid ""
"In this tutorial, you've learned how to write custom Nix modules to bring "
"external services under declarative control, with the help of several new "
"utility functions from the Nixpkgs `lib`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:1234
msgid ""
"You defined several modules in multiple files, each with separate submodules "
"making use of the module system's type checking."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:1236
msgid ""
"These modules exposed features of the external API in a declarative way."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/module-system/deep-dive.md:1238
msgid "You can now conquer the world with Nix."
msgstr ""
